    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) features the high-revving 3.6L M96/03 flat-six engine equipped with VarioCam Plus for optimized torque delivery across the rev range. The powertrain is mated to a G96 6-speed manual transaxle, offering short, tactile throws and precise engagement. Mechanical highlights include a documented LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and a recently replaced rear main seal (RMS), addressing key platform concerns. The suspension retains its factory-correct geometry with McPherson struts up front and a multi-link rear setup, ensuring the communicative handling characteristics the 911 is known for. Braking performance is sharp, aided by four-piston monobloc calipers and cross-drilled rotors. While the exterior shows minor stone chips consistent with a 'good' condition driver, the engine exhibits strong vacuum and zero signs of bore scoring, making this an mechanically sound example for the purist driver.",
